        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nChest pain\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports experiencing persistent, dull chest pain for the past three weeks. The pain is described as a tightness and is not sharp. It is worse with exertion and relieved by rest. He denies shortness of breath, palpitations, or fever. He reports a family history of coronary artery disease.\nFindings\nBlood pressure 130/80 mmHg, heart rate 72 bpm, regular rhythm. Auscultation reveals normal heart sounds. Lung sounds are clear bilaterally.\nAssessment\nChest pain, etiology uncertain. Differential includes musculoskeletal pain, angina, and anxiety.\nPlan\nOrder ECG, troponin, and chest X-ray. Counsel patient on risk factors for coronary artery disease and the importance of lifestyle modifications. Schedule follow-up in 24-48 hours to review results and assess stability.",
